   {:e #blake3 "68ab1655c0915e9a38ca803d225f74be007007356d1c8f479ca734516d1cd767" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Integration test for the entire C9 pipeline. The acceptance criterion for the C9 EPIC: braid seed surfaces convergent audit findings without reading markdown files. This test validates the end-to-end flow. RATIONALE: The C9 insight was discovered when an agent couldn't synthesize 226 audit observations from 4 independent agents. The test recreates this scenario and verifies the system handles it. APPROACH: (1) UNIT TESTS for C9-1: test_corroboration_single_agent (1 agent, score=1/1), test_corroboration_multi_agent (4 agents, 3 agree on same finding, score=3/4), test_corroboration_no_overlap (4 agents, all different topics, each cluster has score=1/4). Property: corroboration_score is always in [0,1] and monotonically non-decreasing as confirming agents are added. (2) UNIT TESTS for C9-2: test_dependency_extraction_basic (observation body with 'depends on t-abcd1234' produces link), test_dependency_extraction_finding_ids (body with 'interacts with F-INV-001' produces link), test_dependency_extraction_no_refs (body with no references produces empty vec), test_dependency_extraction_dedup (same ref mentioned twice produces one link). (3) UNIT TESTS for C9-3: test_seed_corroboration_ranking (convergent findings rank above single-agent), test_seed_budget_preservation (convergent findings survive budget truncation), test_seed_staleness_decay (old convergent findings decay below fresh observations). (4) UNIT TESTS for C9-4: test_contradiction_severity_mismatch (one says Critical, another Low, contradiction flagged), test_no_false_positive (all agree on Critical, no contradiction). (5) UNIT TESTS for C9-5: test_stagnation_detection (5 sessions at 0.62, GoalDrift emitted), test_no_false_alarm (F(S) moving from 0.62 to 0.68, no GoalDrift), test_stagnation_clears (after F(S) moves, GoalDrift clears). (6) E2E TEST scripts/e2e_c9_second_order.sh: Create a fresh store. Simulate 4 agents creating observations about the same 3 findings. Run braid seed --task 'synthesize'. Verify seed output contains: (a) the 3 findings ranked by corroboration, (b) dependency chain if referenced, (c) no markdown file reads needed. Assert exit code 0 and output contains 'corroboration' or 'agents agree'. FAILURE DIAGNOSTICS: Each test logs: observation count, cluster count, corroboration scores, dependency link count, seed section headers. If corroboration detection fails: log embedding similarity matrix and clustering threshold. If dependency extraction fails: log regex matches and parsed references. If seed ranking fails: log scoring components for each candidate. ACCEPTANCE: All unit tests pass. E2E script exits 0. Combined: braid seed output for multi-agent audit scenario surfaces convergent findings first. DEPENDS-ON: C9-1 (t-6090a2ed), C9-2 (t-03f867f7), C9-3 (t-c910d6b2), C9-4 (t-b569197c), C9-5 (t-1a20a2e9). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/tests/ (new c9_second_order.rs), scripts/e2e_c9_second_order.sh." :op :assert}
